modules.description: Loads and processes S-expressions from a file, applying a conversion function to each Sexp. Works with Async.Sexp.t and string list data types. Useful for parsing configuration files or structured data with optional include directives.

This module provides functions for loading and converting S-expressions from files with support for macro expansion during parsing. It works with S-expressions and file paths, offering operations to load single or multiple S-expressions, apply conversion functions, and handle errors either via `Or_error` or exceptions. Concrete use cases include reading and processing configuration files that use macros or include other files through macro expansion.

This module provides functions to load and convert S-expressions from files, with support for handling include directives. It works with strings representing file paths and S-expressions, producing parsed values or lists of values wrapped in result and monadic types. Concrete use cases include loading configuration files or data files written in S-expression format, and retrieving the list of files included during parsing.

This module handles loading and processing S-expressions from files with support for macro expansion and include directives. It operates on S-expressions and file paths, providing functions to load and convert single or multiple S-expressions, track included files, and handle errors. Use cases include parsing configuration files that reference other files or use macros for code generation.
